Thank you everyone for all of your support, constructive criticism and giving me something to do. I wish you all the best of luck for the rest of your lives. There comes a time in everyone here's life where you realize what you are doing and really think about it. Playing a game where the objective is to raise levels, defeat dragons and finish quests? To me now that I think about it, I think that it is pretty childish, but don't get me wrong, yes it is fun and exciting but in the long run, what do you win (in real life)? So, I need to get on with my life and persue myself, because seriously, what do you win in real life?...losing some of your friends because you'd rather play moparscape instead of hang out with them?
Seriously...
